MGS-Toolbox

A comprehensive suite of Python tools and automated pipelines designed to enhance genealogy research. This toolbox specializes in bulk data conversion, LLM-powered historical document transcription, and direct SQLite database management for RootsMagic and Family Tree Maker.

Overview

The MGS-Toolbox is managed via a centralized graphical user interface (GUI) that handles environment configurations securely. The tools range from cleaning up historical county jurisdictions to extracting French-Canadian Catholic parish registers into structured GEDCOM files using the Google Gemini API.

Core Architecture

MGS Toolbox GUI (MGSToolbox.py)

Historical Register Extractor (gather_data.py)

Register to GEDCOM Converter (create_gedcom.py)

Census to GEDCOM Converter (convert_census_1850-1870.py)

RootsMagic Duplicate Finder (Dupes.py)

Historical County Fixer (CountyFix.py)

Gemini Cache Cleanup (cleanup_cache.py)

🛠️ Requirements & Setup

Prerequisites

Python 3.8+

Dependencies: Install the required packages via pip. We strongly recommend using a virtual environment (venv).

pip install pandas geopandas shapely thefuzz python-dotenv tqdm google-genai customtkinter pillow


Configuration & The GUI

You no longer need to manually edit .env files. Simply launch the main GUI to manage all settings, API keys, and directory paths.

python MGSToolbox.py


The GUI will automatically generate and update a local .env file securely, passing the necessary dynamic variables to whichever background script you choose to execute. All script outputs and progress bars are routed directly into the GUI console.

Sample .env Configuration

If you prefer to set up your environment manually or want to see how the GUI structures your data, here is the standard anonymized .env format:

# ==========================================
